# =======================================================
# ACT 3 - Scene 17: Faith in Flaws (Empathy Path)
# File: a3_s17_faith_in_flaws_emp.rpy
# Type: LYRA DEEPENING EROTIC
# =======================================================

# ========= SCENE START TASKS =========
$ _current_scene_id = "a3_s17_faith_in_flaws_emp"
$ scene_mark(_current_scene_id, "entered")

label a3_s17_faith_in_flaws_emp:


    # Gallery — unlock this scene in the character replay grid.
    $ gallery_unlock("a3_s17_faith_in_flaws_emp")
    # ========= STAGE DIRECTIONS (cinema-first) =========
    # CAMERA: 32mm lens (EMP warmth), handheld with barely perceptible sway — breathing camera.
    #         Opens wide on the observation deck: Lyra at the railing, city below.
    #         Tightens as Aeron joins. Two-shot that slowly becomes profile close-ups.
    #         When the breathing syncs: the camera sway matches their rhythm. Felt, not shown.
    #         Intimacy: locked frame. No movement. The stillness IS the shot.
    # LIGHTING: Observation deck: city glow from below (amber, shifting), cool moonlight from above.
    #           Ghostline relay light (distant green pulse) in the periphery.
    #           Faces lit from below — inverted from the usual. Vulnerability in the uplighting.
    #           Intimacy: amber dominates. The city light is warm enough to be kind.
    #           Aftercare: moonlight only. Cool, clean. Foreheads together in silver light.
    # SFX: Loop — wind, distant city thrum, faint Ghostline carrier hum (musical, not harsh).
    #      One-shots — railing creak, fabric shift, breath catches (in sync), hair in wind.
    #      The breathing sync: audible. Two rhythms becoming one without effort.
    # FX/COMP: City sprawl below — lights like a circuit board. Wind moving hair and fabric.
    #          The observation deck railing: metal, cool, familiar from Act 1 balcony scenes.
    # BLOCKING: Lyra at the railing. Aeron joins. They stand side by side — Act 1 balcony echo.
    #           But there's no audience here. No gala below. No performance.
    #           Physical proximity increases through the scene — shoulders, hands, foreheads.
    # CANON: DEEPENING erotic for Lyra. Not first — that was Breath of Faith (s03).
    #        The emotional texture is confident and warm, not desperate or searching.
    #        Faith-through-vulnerability arc culmination for Act 3.
    #        The breathing sync: established in s03 and the field sync (s10). Now it happens without trying.
    #        Callbacks: Act 1 balcony (s07), s03 Breath of Faith, s08 Unmeasurable, s10 field sync.
    # CONSENT: 3-gate framework. (A) Verbal — Act 1 callback. (B) Physical — mirrors shared light.
    #          (C) Explicit — "That's enough. But I want more."

    # ========= VOICE BASELINE =========
    # EMP cadence: Contractions, sensory language, emotional warmth.
    # Lyra: Articulate but softer than Act 1. The formality has dissolved into something genuine.
    #       Her faith language is personal now — not doctrine, not performance. Lived theology.
    # Aeron: Present. Not analyzing. The static has been quiet long enough that he can feel without filtering.

    # --- VISUAL SETUP ---
    # [EXT. PHOENIX BASE - OBSERVATION DECK - NIGHT]
    # A platform on the upper level with a clear view of the city below.
    # The lights spread out like a living map. Wind moves through the deck in slow gusts.

    #scene bg_observation_deck_night_emp with dissolve
    #play ambient "sfx/ambient/observation_wind_warm.ogg" fadein 2.0
    #play music "music/lyra_theme_intimate.ogg" fadein 3.0

    # --- OPENING: LYRA ALONE ---

    "The observation deck is empty except for one figure at the railing."

    "Lyra stands with her hands resting on the metal rail, watching the city breathe below. The wind moves through her hair. She doesn't correct it."

    athought "She used to arrange her hair. Part of the architecture of who she was presenting."

    athought "Now she lets the wind have it."

    "He doesn't announce himself. She knows he's there."

    l "The city looks different from up here."

    a "Different how?"

    l "From the balcony at the gala, it looked like a stage set. Something arranged for the audience."

    l "From here it just looks... alive. Messy. Unfinished."

    athought "She's been thinking about the balcony. So have I."

    "He joins her at the railing. Shoulder beside shoulder. The same configuration as a hundred quiet moments — but each time the proximity means something different."

    # --- THE CONVERSATION: FAITH IN FLAWS ---

    l "Do you remember what I said about the Unmeasurable?"

    a "The thing the Band can't quantify."

    l "The Order had a word for it. Aneva. The space between what can be measured and what matters."

    l "They treated it like a destination. Like if you meditated long enough, prayed precisely enough, aligned perfectly enough, you'd arrive."

    athought "Her voice has the cadence of someone who's thought about this for months. Not rehearsed — digested."

    a "And now?"

    l "I used to think faith meant being whole. Undamaged. A vessel without cracks."

    l "The Order taught that the divine moved through perfection. Perfect ritual. Perfect alignment. Perfect stillness."

    "She turns her hands over on the railing. Palms up. The Band edge is visible at her left wrist — she doesn't hide it anymore."

    l "I spent years trying to be that vessel. Smoothing every flaw. Sealing every crack."

    a "What changed?"

    l "You."

    athought "The word lands like a stone in still water."

    l "Not in some romantic, redemptive way. I don't mean you saved me."

    l "I mean you're the most cracked vessel I've ever met. And the divine — whatever's left of it — moves through you anyway."

    athought "I don't know what to do with that."

    l "You carry your father's methodology in your bones. You trained as a weapon. You spent years dulled by suppressants, performing empathy instead of feeling it."

    l "And despite all of that — because of all of that — you chose to feel. You chose to stay."

    l "That's not perfection. That's faith in flaws."

    athought "Faith in flaws."

    athought "She's not describing me. She's describing what she believes."

    athought "And what she believes is that the cracks are the proof. That the breaking is what lets the light in."

    a "Lyra—"

    l "I have faith in your flaws because they're the proof you're human."

    l "The Order got it wrong. The divine doesn't move through perfect vessels. It moves through the broken ones who keep standing."

    "She looks at him. The city light from below catches her face — amber, shifting. The uplighting is unflattering by any standard, and she's never been more beautiful."

    athought "I'm not going to tell her that. She'd argue. She'd say beauty isn't the point."

    athought "She'd be right. And she'd still be beautiful."

    # --- THE BREATHING ---

    "He realizes it before she does."

    athought "Our breathing."

    athought "It synced."

    athought "Not like the exercise on the balcony — that was guided. Deliberate. Lyra counting, me following."

    athought "This is just... happening. Inhale. Exhale. The same rhythm."

    athought "Neither of us started it."

    "She notices. He sees the moment it registers — a slight widening of her eyes, a pause in the middle of an exhale."

    l "Aeron."

    a "I know."

    l "We're—"

    "He meets her eyes. She closes her mouth. Opens it again."

    l "That used to take twenty minutes of guided practice."

    a "It's been doing this for a while, hasn't it."

    l "Since the field sync. Maybe before."

    athought "Since the field sync. The operation where our breathing matched without trying, and we moved through the corridor like one person in two bodies."

    athought "Since before that. Since the balcony. Since the first time she put her hands on mine and said 'breathe with me.'"

    "The wind shifts. It carries the faint carrier hum of the Ghostline — musical, almost. The sound Zira's network makes when it's working."

    "Their breathing doesn't break."

    l "The Order would say this means we've achieved alignment."

    a "What do you say?"

    l "I say we're just two people who've learned each other's rhythm."

    l "And that's better than alignment."

    # --- BUILD-UP ---

    "She turns from the railing. Faces him."

    athought "The Act 1 balcony. The gala. Her in the green dress, me in the uniform I didn't deserve."

    athought "There was an audience then. Hundreds of faces below. The performance of connection over drinks and ambient music."

    athought "No audience now. No gala. No dress. Just Lyra in field clothes with wind-tangled hair, and me."

    athought "This is better."

    "She steps closer. Not urgently — with the certainty of someone who knows exactly how much distance there is and how much of it she wants to close."

    # --- CONSENT GATE A: Verbal - Act 1 Callback ---

    l "Do you remember the balcony?"

    a "Every detail."

    l "I wore a dress I hated. You held a glass you didn't drink."

    a "And you talked about the hum beneath things. The frequency the Cores make."

    l "I was trying so hard to be the person I thought you needed."

    a "You were already the person I needed. I just didn't know how to say it."

    athought "She's close enough now that I can count the colors in her eyes. Brown, gold, a ring of dark amber near the pupil."

    athought "I've memorized them. That happened without my permission."

    # --- CONSENT GATE B: Physical - Mirrors Shared Light ---

    "She reaches for him. Her hands find his. The same hands from the breathing exercise — but there's no tremor to steady this time."

    "Her thumbs trace his knuckles. The touch mirrors the shared light moment from Act 1 — when she'd held his hands and he'd felt something pass between them that neither of them named."

    athought "She's doing it again. The circuit. Her skin against mine and something flowing through the contact."

    athought "Not mystical. Not the Cores. Not divine."

    athought "Just her."

    "She presses her forehead against his. The breathing is still synced. Inhale. Exhale. Their breath mingles in the cold air between them."

    # --- CONSENT GATE C: Explicit ---

    l "We can just breathe. That's enough."

    a "It's enough."

    "A beat."

    a "But I want more."

    "She pulls back just far enough to see his eyes."

    l "More."

    a "More of you. All the parts you used to hide behind the ceremony."

    l "I'm not hiding anymore."

    a "I know."

    "She kisses him."

    "It's different from the balcony. Different from Breath of Faith. The searching is gone. She knows what she's looking for and she found it."

    athought "Her mouth is warm. The wind moves around us but doesn't touch the space between."

    athought "Her hands move from mine to my shoulders. Not pulling — steadying. Grounding herself the way she taught me to ground."

    athought "I put my hands on her waist and feel her breathing against my palms."

    athought "Still synced."

    # [INTIMATE CONTENT HERE]

    # ========== AFTERCARE ==========

    "After."

    "The observation deck. The city still breathing below. The wind has settled into something gentler."

    "Foreheads pressed together. His hands on her waist. Her fingers in his hair."

    athought "No words."

    athought "We don't need them."

    athought "The breathing is still synced. It never stopped."

    "The moonlight has shifted — cooler now, silver-white. It catches the edge of her jaw, the line of her neck, the Band at her wrist."

    "She doesn't hide it. Doesn't cover it."

    athought "That's its own kind of faith."

    l "..."

    athought "She whispers something. Her lips move against my forehead."

    athought "It might be a prayer. It might be my name."

    athought "I don't ask which."

    athought "I don't think the distinction matters."

    "The Ghostline carrier hum fills the space around them. The wind carries it. Musical. Warm."

    "Their breathing holds its rhythm."

    l "(barely audible) Still synced."

    a "(same) Still synced."

    athought "She smiles against my skin. I feel it more than see it."

    athought "The city turns below us. The cracks in everything are where the light gets in."

    athought "She taught me that."

    athought "She's still teaching me."

    "The wind picks up. She presses closer. Not against the cold — into the warmth."

    "They stay."

    #stop music fadeout 4.0
    #stop ambient fadeout 3.0
    #scene black with fade

    # ========= STATE UPDATES =========
    $ rel_bump("Lyra", trust=1, affection=2)
    $ nudge_poly(1)
    $ scene_mark(_current_scene_id, "completed")

    return


